# Brand Compliance Review
# Demonstrates how a custom AI skill audits marketing assets against brand
# guidelines — scoring files across voice, visual identity, messaging, and
# consistency, then producing a prioritized remediation plan.

[section: setup]

Before running this demo:
1. Upload uppababy-brand-guidelines-ai-extracted.md to the site's document library
2. Confirm the brand-review skill is installed in Agent Assets > Skills
3. Have the demo files ready locally:
   - cruz-v3-launch.pptx
   - retailer-training-q4.pptx
   - social-media-content-brief.docx
   - spring-2026-creative-brief.docx

[navigate: https://microsoft.sharepoint-df.com/teams/ZachDemos/]

[open-chat]

[new-chat]

[section: demo]

[navigate: https://microsoft.sharepoint-df.com/teams/ZachDemos/]

A brand manager has a problem: the team produces a constant stream of marketing
assets — launch decks, retailer training, social briefs, creative briefs. Each one
is supposed to follow brand guidelines. But reviewing each file manually against
a 40-page brand guide doesn't scale.

Let's show how a custom skill can do this automatically, at any scale, with
specific and actionable feedback.

[pause]

[open-chat]

We'll start with the product launch deck. I'm going to attach it and ask the
brand-review skill to evaluate it.

[upload: demos/UPPABaby Brand Review/cruz-v3-launch.pptx]

[prompt: Use the brand-review skill to evaluate this file for UPPAbaby brand compliance.]

[wait]

The agent read the brand definition reference, identified the file type and intended
channel, then scored the deck across five weighted categories: Voice and Tone,
Visual Identity, Messaging Alignment, Photography and Imagery, and Brand
Consistency.

Notice the output: an overall compliance rating, then a tiered list of issues —
Critical, Major, Minor — each with a specific, concrete fix. Not "improve your
tone." Actual actionable steps.

[pause]

Let's run the same review on the retailer training deck. Different audience,
different channel — let's see if the issues differ.

[upload: demos/UPPABaby Brand Review/retailer-training-q4.pptx]

[prompt: Use the brand-review skill to evaluate this file for UPPAbaby brand compliance.]

[wait]

Different results — the retailer deck has different compliance issues because the
brand expectations for a channel-facing training deck differ from a launch
presentation. The skill reasons about context, not just keyword matching.

[pause]

One more — a creative brief. This is internal-facing, which changes what the skill
looks for.

[upload: demos/UPPABaby Brand Review/spring-2026-creative-brief.docx]

[prompt: Use the brand-review skill to evaluate this file for UPPAbaby brand compliance.]

[wait]

A brief scores differently from a deck — the skill understands that a brief isn't
consumer-facing and adjusts its evaluation accordingly. You're not getting false
positives for things that don't matter in this context.

[screenshot: tools/screenshots/brand-review.png]

What you just saw: three different file types, three different channels, one skill,
consistent evaluation criteria. Each review takes seconds. Each result is grounded
in the brand definition document you uploaded — not a generic AI opinion.

The skill works across PPTX, DOCX, PDFs, images, and plain text. Any file the
brand team produces, the agent can audit.

[pause]

